{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.6","role":"article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"TestStore\/receive(_:_:timeout:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-9jd7x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method when you need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assert on the payload inside an action received."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Asserting on action payloads","anchor":"Asserting-on-action-payloads","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In version 1.4 of the library we provided a new assertion method on "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"tex